gomodel:SYNGO_895  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Neurexin-1beta without an insert in splice site 4 (SS4-) regulates mEPSC frequency in cultured cortical neurons. Fig. 3 shows that this isoform rescues the decrease in mEPSC frequency that occurs in cultured triple neurexin-1/2/3beta KO neurons.\n\nFig. 4 shows that the decrease in mEPSC frequency in absence of all beta-neurexins is correlated with an increase in endocannabinoid signaling that originates in the postsynaptic neurons. This indicates that the abovementioned presynaptic neurexin-1beta rescue of excitatory miniature release may involve a regulation of postsynaptic endocannabinoid signaling.. Experimental description: Neurexin-beta triple floxed mice were generated by homologous recombination targeting the 50 unique exon for each of the three beta-neurexin genes that is not shared with its alpha-neurexin counterparts.\n\n12/10/2017 Pim\n- Literal: \"All neurexin-1β rescue constructs were previously described mouse cDNAs expressed from separate lentiviruses (Aoto et al., 2013)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-05" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_895" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

